NarNarrative: The skeletons of British Toads can be distinguished from those of Frogs by their shorter legs and the shape of the pelvic diapophysis (the vertebra furthest from the head), both of which are visible in this dorsal view.

This is an Olm preserved in 'spirit' (a mixture of ethanol and methanol). Olms are amphibians that live in pools in caves, and are found in Yugoslavia. Spirit preserves of the soft parts of an animal which would otherwise shrivel away, but the specimens often quickly lose their colour.
